                        "content": "The nurse in a primary health care provider setting is calculating a client’s body mass index (BMI). The nurse determines the client’s BMI is 30.2 kg/m2. How would the nurse classify the client’s BMI based on this value?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "11797937e327eb6d913faa80427c566b",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Analyzing 分析",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nObesity is defined as an increase in body weight beyond the body’s physical requirements that results in an abnormal accumulation of fat cells. BMI categories consist of underweight, normal, overweight, obesity, and extreme obesity. Underweight is defined as a BMI of less than 18.5 kg/m2. Normal weight is defined as a BMI from 18.5 to 24.9 kg/m2. Overweight is defined as a BMI from 25.0 to 29.9 kg/m2. Obesity is defined as a BMI from 30.0 to 39.9 kg/m2. Morbid or extreme obesity is defined as a BMI greater than or equal to 40.0 kg/m2. Therefore, option 1 is correct because the client’s BMI falls into the obese range.",
