                        "content": "The nurse in a primary health care provider setting is assessing an obese male client for risk factors of metabolic syndrome. Based on the assessment, the nurse determines that which finding is a risk factor for metabolic syndrome?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "11797937e327eb6d913faa80427c566b",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Analyzing 分析",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nThe diagnostic measures for metabolic syndrome differ between males and females. Three of the five following criteria must be present for metabolic syndrome to be diagnosed: waist circumference equal to or greater than 35 inches (89 cm) in females and equal to or greater than 40 inches (102 centimeters) in males; triglycerides greater than 150 mg/dL (1.7 mmol/L) or drug treatment for high triglycerides; high-density lipoprotein (HDL) cholesterol less than 40 mg/dL (0.9 mmol/L) in males and less than 50 mg/dL (1.1 mmol/L) in females or drug treatment for hyperlipidemia; systolic blood pressure equal to or greater than 130 mm Hg, diastolic blood pressure equal to or greater than 85 mm Hg or treatment for hypertension; or fasting blood glucose greater than or equal to 100 mg/dL (5.6 mmol/L). Since a waist circumference of 40 inches or (102 centimeters) in males is a risk factor for metabolic syndrome, option 4 is correct.",
